1. cs.DB (Database): The paper focuses on designing a scalable storage system that can organize a massive amount of unstructured and continuously changing data into multi-dimensional data models. This falls under the scope of database systems. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper discusses the use of predictive and prescriptive analytics techniques, which are commonly used in AI applications. 
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper proposes a new data model called Many-Worlds Graphs, which combines graphs and time series. This falls under the scope of data structures. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper discusses the use of predictive analytics techniques, which are commonly used in machine learning applications. 
5. cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper presents an open source implementation called GreyCat, which can efficiently fork and update thousands of parallel worlds composed of millions of timestamped nodes. This falls under the scope of software engineering.
